PASSENGER INFORMATION
TIMES: The 24-hour clock is used and all times shown are Local Stand-
ard Times, except where Daylight Saving Time is observed. Times shown
between 0:01
(1 minute after midnight) and 12:00 (noon) are
A.M.
times and are shown in lightface type. Times shown from 12:01 to 24:00
are P.M. times and are shown in boldface type. To convert P.M. times
to 12-hour clock, subtract 12 hours.
Carriers: All flights are operated by Pan American World Airways, Inc.
(PAA), except where indicated as National (NA), Pan American-Grace
Airways (PANAGRA), Braniff (BN), Delta (DL) and Panair do Brasil
(PAB).
PASSPORTS, VISAS, VACCINATION CERTIFICATES: To travel
from one country to another you must usually have a valid passport, vIsa
Foother permit when Us, amall racination certificate is required
unless you are coming directly from Aruba, Bahamas, Bermuda, Curacao,
Iceland, Jamaica or Virgin Islands.
STOPOVERS: Permitted at scheduled stops when arranged in advance.
BAGGAGE: The general free allowances for passengers paying adult
fares are: 30 kilograms (66 Ibs.) on First Class Services; 20 kilograms
(44 lbs.) on Economy,
Tourist & Thrift Class Services. Where travel is
partly via
First Class and partly via Economy, Tourist or Thrift Class
the free allowance for each portion is that applicable to the class of
service for which the fare is paid.
